# Architecture & File Conventions

Canonical layout: [`docs/BLUEPRINT.md`](../../docs/BLUEPRINT.md)

## Flat `tests/` — no tier folders

```text
tests/
├── landing.spec.ts
├── add-remove-elements.spec.ts
└── dynamic-controls.spec.ts
```

**Forbidden:**

- Subfolders: `tests/smoke/`, `tests/regression/`, `tests/e2e/`
- Tier suffixes: `*.smoke.spec.ts`, `*.regression.spec.ts`
- Execution intent in paths — use tags in titles: `@smoke`, `@regression`

Filter suites at runtime: `npm run test:smoke` → `--grep @smoke`

## Kebab-case filenames only

All files under `src/` and `tests/` **must** use kebab-case:

| ✅ Allowed | ❌ Forbidden |
| --- | --- |
| `add-remove-elements.page.ts` | `AddRemoveElements.page.ts` |
| `dynamic-controls.spec.ts` | `dynamicControls.spec.ts` |
| `navigation.map.ts` | `navigationMap.ts` |

> TypeScript **class names** inside files remain PascalCase (`AddRemoveElementsPage`).

## Layer boundaries

| Layer | Owns | Must NOT own |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `src/pages/` | `readonly` locators, user actions | `expect()` assertions |
| `tests/` | assertions, `@smoke`/`@regression` tags, `test.describe` groups | raw locators, direct `@playwright/test` import |
| `src/fixtures/` | custom `test` export, page injection | business logic |
| `src/data/` | maps, builders, env credentials | DOM interaction |
| `src/config/` | `environments.ts`, `test-tags.ts` | locators |

## Required imports

```typescript
// ✅ Specs
import { test, expect } from '@fixtures';

// ❌ Specs
import { test, expect } from '@playwright/test';
```

## Path aliases (mandatory)

`@fixtures` · `@pages/*` · `@data/*` · `@config/*` · `@utils/*`

No deep relative imports (`../../../src/pages/...`) in new code.

## One file per feature

Happy paths and negative/edge cases live in the **same** spec file, grouped by `test.describe` — never split across tier files.
